Introduction

Lue Younghoon, also known simply as Younghoon, is a South Korean singer and former member of the boy groups Seven O’Clock, Black Level, and the pre-debut group VI'ENX. He first debuted under the stage name 2Soul in 2017 as a member of Seven O’Clock with their mini album Butterfly Effect. During his time with the group, he participated in the survival show MIXNINE, though he was not selected as an official contestant. After Seven O’Clock disbanded in 2021, he re-debuted with Black Level in 2022 with the mini album New-Start, but left the group later that year. In 2023, he joined VI'ENX, though he appeared to have left the group by April 2024.

In September 2024, Younghoon competed in the survival show Project 7, where he was officially introduced as a contestant. However, he was eliminated in episode 8 after ranking 53rd. Following his time on the show, he announced his solo debut under the name Lue Younghoon, releasing his first single album "Untold Story" on February 12, 2025.
